<p>Suppose there are four divs in parent if one div has been deleted by client side then other divs fill the blank space and auto adjust width ... parent div does not change his width and height  child divs dynamicaly append in the parent div i have tried with css but there no any asolution about it</p>  <p>HTML:</p>  <pre><code>first picture &lt;div id="parent" style="height:300px"&gt;    &lt;div id="child1" class="child"&gt; first child box &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;div id="child2" class="child"&gt; second child box &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;div id="child3" class="child"&gt; third child box &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;div id="child4" class="child"&gt;fourth child box &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;br&gt;second pictrue after delted child box &lt;div id="parent2" style="height:300px"&gt;    &lt;div id="child1" class="child"&gt; first child box &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;div id="child2" class="child"&gt; second child box &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;div id="child3" class="child" style="width:94%"&gt; third child box &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;button onclick="removeLastChild();"&gt;Remove&lt;/button&gt; </code></pre>  <p>CSS:</p>  <pre><code>.child{     height:125px;     width:45%;     margin:2%;     float:left;     background-color:red; } #parent {     background-color:grey;     width:300px;     height:auto;  } #parent2 {     background-color:grey;     width:300px;     height:auto;  } </code></pre>  <p>See <a href="http://jsfiddle.net/5rfn10rh/3/" rel="nofollow">http://jsfiddle.net/5rfn10rh/3/</a>; delete any child box then other box will adjust and cover the deleted box (adjust auto width) fist picture and second picture you can see now in fiddle</p>